# Final Project Summary

**Internship:** ApexPlanet Software Pvt Ltd — Web Development (PHP & MySQL)
**Duration:** 45 Days
**Project:** Blog CRUD Application with Authentication & Security

---

## Overview

Over the course of this internship, I built a complete blog-style web application from scratch using **PHP and MySQL**, progressing through 5 structured tasks — from setting up a local development environment to delivering a fully tested, secure, production-style application.

---

## What Was Built

A web application where users can:
- Register and log in securely
- Create, view, edit, and delete blog posts
- Search posts by title or content
- Browse posts through paginated results
- Experience role-based permissions — only **admin** users can delete posts, while **editors** can create and edit

---

## Task-by-Task Summary

**Task 1 — Development Environment Setup (3 Days)**
Set up a local PHP/MySQL server using XAMPP, installed VS Code as the code editor, and configured Git version control with an initial commit pushed to a GitHub repository.

**Task 2 — Basic CRUD Application (10 Days)**
Designed the MySQL database (`blog`) with `users` and `posts` tables. Built the core Create, Read, Update, and Delete functionality for posts, along with user registration and login using session-based authentication and bcrypt password hashing.

**Task 3 — Advanced Features Implementation (10 Days)**
Added a search feature to filter posts by title/content, implemented pagination to limit posts per page with navigation, and improved the interface with custom CSS styling for a cleaner, more professional look.

**Task 4 — Security Enhancements (10 Days)**
Reinforced the application against common vulnerabilities: all SQL queries use prepared statements to prevent SQL injection, added client-side and server-side form validation, and introduced role-based access control (admin vs. editor) so only authorized users can perform sensitive actions like deleting posts.

**Task 5 — Final Project and Certification (12 Days)**
Integrated everything into one cohesive application and performed structured end-to-end testing — covering the full user flow, CRUD operations, search/pagination accuracy, and security checks (rejecting weak passwords, blocking unauthenticated access to protected pages, and confirming role-based restrictions). All tests passed, resulting in a polished, fully functional application.

